<function>

access:   public

name: quote

param: mixed, $val

return: string

</function>

Safely quotes a value for an SQL statement.

* Parameters:

 * mixed //$val//: The value to quote.

* Returns string: An SQL-safe quoted value (or a string of  separated-and-quoted values).

Safely quotes a value for an SQL statement.

If an array is passed as the value, the array values are quoted
and then returned as a comma-separated string; this is useful 
for generating IN() lists.

<code type="php">
$sql = Solar::factory('Solar_Sql');

$safe = $sql->quote('foo"bar"');
// $safe == "'foo\"bar\"'"

$safe = $sql->quote(array('one', 'two', 'three'));
// $safe == "'one', 'two', 'three'"
</code>